      <h1>The Coordination Reform</h1>
            
    
</div>

<div class="documentBody">
    <p><strong><img alt="" hspace="3" src="/upload/HOD/Ingresssbilder/Profil_samhandlingsreformen.jpg" align="left" vspace="3" /></strong></p>
<p><strong>In the course of April 2009 the Minister of Health and Social Affairs Bjarne Håkon Hanssen will present a new health reform, a coordination reform, for the health service. The minister’s own team of experts will help him to find the economic and legal tack for meeting the challenges in the Norwegian health sector.</strong> <br /><br /><br />“Norway spends the most money in the world on health, but does not get the most health in return for each krone. It’s the system that’s at fault. A lack of contact between hospitals and local authorities is the principal obstacle to making the health service even better. This is a problem that we are now going to do something about. Coordination will take place on the basis of existing systems, not in spite of them,” says Bjarne Håkon Hanssen.<br /><br /><br /></p>
    
    

        
        

<div class="ArticleView">
        <img src="/upload/HOD/Portrettbilder/Ekspertutvalget/samlet_ingress.jpg" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
        
        
        <div class="ArticleImgContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/hod/kampanjer/the-coordination-reform/team-of-experts.html?id=524785">Team of experts</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               The minister’s own team of experts will help him to find the economic and legal tack for meeting the challenges in the Norwegian health sector. 
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    


<div class="ArticleView">
        
        
        
        <div class="ArticleImgContent">
